1
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:10,800
"Blue Lips"

2
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:13,700
(Episode 4)

3
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:39,880
Something's not right.

4
00:01:41,239 --> 00:01:43,158
How come every time Brother Mo shows up,

5
00:01:43,159 --> 00:01:45,679
Xiao Wu switches to these
tender, romantic songs?

6
00:01:47,219 --> 00:01:49,099
He changes the song,
and you change your drink.

7
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:52,720
Could he be singing
them specifically for you?

8
00:01:53,719 --> 00:01:55,119
What are you talking about?

9
00:01:55,519 --> 00:01:57,239
You know exactly what our relationship is.

10
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:01,160
Where's my Long Island Iced Tea?

11
00:02:02,340 --> 00:02:03,340
Right.

12
00:02:15,380 --> 00:02:16,380
Xiao Wu.

13
00:02:18,219 --> 00:02:20,459
The guests at that table are
waiting for you to go over.

14
00:02:30,119 --> 00:02:31,439
Looking handsome as always today.

15
00:02:31,719 --> 00:02:32,940
What's wrong? Not happy?

16
00:02:33,739 --> 00:02:34,900
I bought you a few bottles.

17
00:02:35,159 --> 00:02:36,900
If you ever need anything in the future,

18
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:38,420
just call me anytime.

19
00:02:42,820 --> 00:02:44,476
Why the attitude when
you're out having fun?

20
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:47,420
I brought so many people here and
you're just going to have that attitude?

21
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:54,380
Drink this glass,

22
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,139
and we'll call it an apology.

23
00:03:10,119 --> 00:03:11,879
He's a singer who draws
in such a big crowd.

24
00:03:12,420 --> 00:03:14,340
Are you really going
to let him drink like that?

25
00:03:14,579 --> 00:03:15,779
That's a bit unfair, isn't it?

26
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:18,380
Look who's talking.

27
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:20,200
Blue Moon is a respectable place.

28
00:03:21,559 --> 00:03:22,780
We're all looking out for him.

29
00:03:25,159 --> 00:03:26,159
Besides,

30
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:27,460
the kid needs the money.

31
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:30,035
He's willing to drink with customers.

32
00:03:30,059 --> 00:03:32,539
Who wouldn't want to make
some extra cash while they're young?

33
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:34,420
He knows his limits.

34
00:03:41,539 --> 00:03:43,019
If I book that booth,

35
00:03:43,380 --> 00:03:44,620
can I get him to drink with me?

36
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,800
Why? Do you want to try?

37
00:04:02,179 --> 00:04:05,218
Brother Hao, let me explain.
I was just playing around with him.

38
00:04:05,243 --> 00:04:07,643
[An extremely smarmy string of
texts pining after Wu Shixian]

39
00:04:10,659 --> 00:04:12,859
If you were just playing
around, why are you panicking?

40
00:04:16,659 --> 00:04:18,940
I heard you go to Blue Moon
every day to listen to music

41
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,300
just because of him.

42
00:04:21,559 --> 00:04:22,099
Brother Hao.

43
00:04:22,426 --> 00:04:23,786
He's the one who seduced me first.

44
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:25,000
When he was seducing me,

45
00:04:25,219 --> 00:04:27,059
you were the only one
on my mind, Brother Hao.

46
00:04:31,099 --> 00:04:32,135
You were flirting with him like crazy,

47
00:04:32,159 --> 00:04:33,380
and he completely ignored you.

48
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,539
And you're telling me he seduced you?

49
00:04:38,599 --> 00:04:39,940
Do you think I'm blind?

50
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,300
No...

51
00:04:47,159 --> 00:04:48,159
You...

52
00:04:48,659 --> 00:04:51,059
Even though you've only been
with me for a couple of months,

53
00:04:51,519 --> 00:04:53,179
we still have some history.

54
00:04:54,119 --> 00:04:55,899
While I'm still letting
you keep some dignity,

55
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,280
get the hell out of here.

56
00:04:57,639 --> 00:04:58,639
Let him go.

57
00:05:00,679 --> 00:05:01,159
Brother Hao!

58
00:05:01,539 --> 00:05:02,796
You're really the only one in my heart!

59
00:05:02,820 --> 00:05:03,820
Brother Hao!

60
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:04,960
Drag him out.

61
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:09,015
Guan Zhenghao, who the
hell do you think you are?

62
00:05:09,039 --> 00:05:10,319
How dare you treat me like this?

63
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:15,900
Guan Zhenghao!

64
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:18,476
Don't think you're a big shot just
because you have some dirty money!

65
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:20,500
You're just a bastard
with no father to raise you!

66
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:22,840
In this world,

67
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,019
no one truly loves you,

68
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:25,700
and no one will ever care about you!

69
00:05:29,019 --> 00:05:30,019
Bury him.

70
00:05:31,219 --> 00:05:32,219
Guan Zhenghao!

71
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,619
You bastard!

72
00:05:56,119 --> 00:05:57,400
This ball is mine.

73
00:05:57,719 --> 00:05:59,659
Hey, can you give it back to me?

74
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,860
Xiao Le, slow down.

75
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:04,840
Xiao Hao.

76
00:06:05,099 --> 00:06:06,979
Why are you bullying
your little brother again?

77
00:06:07,780 --> 00:06:09,079
Xiao Le, right?

78
00:06:10,099 --> 00:06:10,860
This ball...

79
00:06:11,099 --> 00:06:12,099
is mine now.

80
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:14,679
What is wrong with you?

81
00:06:14,719 --> 00:06:15,719
He's your brother!

82
00:06:16,079 --> 00:06:17,800
Does a stepbrother even count as a brother?

83
00:06:18,199 --> 00:06:18,840
Besides,

84
00:06:19,019 --> 00:06:20,360
it's just a toy.

85
00:06:20,659 --> 00:06:21,659
What's the big deal?

86
00:06:22,940 --> 00:06:23,960
He's not like you.

87
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:25,000
You're right.

88
00:06:25,079 --> 00:06:26,440
Of course he's not like me.

89
00:06:30,239 --> 00:06:30,900
Xiao Hao.

90
00:06:31,219 --> 00:06:32,300
Today is your birthday.

91
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,800
I won't scold you.

92
00:06:34,179 --> 00:06:35,859
Go back to your grandmother's house early.

93
00:06:36,239 --> 00:06:37,239
Don't make her worry.

94
00:06:39,559 --> 00:06:40,199
Let's go.

95
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,500
Let's go.

96
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:02,840
Xiao Wu.

97
00:07:03,219 --> 00:07:04,718
The guest in the VIP booth

98
00:07:04,719 --> 00:07:06,039
wants you to go over for a drink.

99
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:12,960
I got it.

100
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,280
Have a seat.

101
00:07:35,019 --> 00:07:36,019
Come on.

102
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:37,260
How do you want to drink?

103
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:38,559
Should we cross arms,

104
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:39,760
or just drink together?

105
00:07:43,059 --> 00:07:44,819
You don't have to drink
when you're with me.

106
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:54,939
Who knows if you've slipped

107
00:07:54,940 --> 00:07:56,679
something strange in here.

108
00:08:08,659 --> 00:08:09,659
Drink up.

109
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,280
Then...

110
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,800
what about all this alcohol?

111
00:08:18,279 --> 00:08:19,279
Return it.

112
00:08:21,859 --> 00:08:22,859
Just kidding.

113
00:08:23,619 --> 00:08:24,619
Is that funny?

114
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,600
That's cold.

115
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:32,620
This booth has a minimum spend.

116
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:35,080
You really went all out this time.

117
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:38,479
I spent a little,

118
00:08:38,739 --> 00:08:39,939
but it's hardly going all out.

119
00:08:40,699 --> 00:08:42,479
Consider it a treat for once.

120
00:08:49,699 --> 00:08:50,760
Are you enjoying it?

121
00:08:51,819 --> 00:08:53,279
There are many ways to enjoy things.

122
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:55,899
This is the first time

123
00:08:56,180 --> 00:08:57,339
I've sat in front of so much alcohol

124
00:08:57,340 --> 00:08:58,460
without taking a single sip.

125
00:09:00,659 --> 00:09:01,659
It feels quite nice.

126
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:04,920
What kind of feeling?

127
00:09:11,579 --> 00:09:12,579
A feeling of solitude.

128
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,300
Do you want to skip work?

129
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,520
What?

130
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:54,800
Even though I'm not a local,

131
00:09:55,979 --> 00:09:56,439
still,

132
00:09:56,659 --> 00:09:58,159
even the locals in Jinyang

133
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:00,780
don't know this place as well as I do.

134
00:10:03,399 --> 00:10:04,399
I don't believe you.

135
00:10:05,159 --> 00:10:06,159
Why not?

136
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,300
This place tonight is the best proof.

137
00:10:12,239 --> 00:10:12,659
By the way,

138
00:10:13,159 --> 00:10:15,079
there's a question I've
been meaning to ask you.

139
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:17,520
Go ahead.

140
00:10:18,340 --> 00:10:20,739
The first time you came to
my shop to buy medicine,

141
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:22,660
there were so many shops on that street.

142
00:10:22,859 --> 00:10:23,859
Why did you choose mine?

143
00:10:28,220 --> 00:10:29,220
Because of...

144
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,740
the light at your storefront, I guess.

145
00:10:39,439 --> 00:10:40,439
The light?

146
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:46,260
The lights at the other shops

147
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:48,100
were either white

148
00:10:48,140 --> 00:10:49,340
or red.

149
00:10:51,039 --> 00:10:52,039
Only your shop's light

150
00:10:52,579 --> 00:10:53,619
was yellow.

151
00:10:55,039 --> 00:10:56,039
I...

152
00:10:57,380 --> 00:10:58,380
I just...

153
00:11:00,279 --> 00:11:01,279
Just because of that?

154
00:11:05,399 --> 00:11:06,920
What else would it be?

155
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:09,100
Because you're handsome?

156
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:12,920
Am I not handsome?

157
00:11:14,539 --> 00:11:15,560
Don't flatter yourself.

158
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,340
Actually,

159
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:21,600
this is...

160
00:11:21,779 --> 00:11:24,039
the best stargazing spot around Jinyang.

161
00:11:24,319 --> 00:11:25,359
Most people can't find it.

162
00:11:25,699 --> 00:11:25,920
Here,

163
00:11:26,319 --> 00:11:27,319
let me show you.

164
00:11:27,619 --> 00:11:28,619
Look,

165
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:30,199
that's Jupiter,

166
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,600
to the west of the moon.

167
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:33,819
And to the north is Sirius.

168
00:11:34,579 --> 00:11:35,119
Further east

169
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:36,220
is Mars.

170
00:11:37,199 --> 00:11:37,659
And then?

171
00:11:37,859 --> 00:11:38,920
The brightness of planets

172
00:11:39,119 --> 00:11:40,239
is much more stable,

173
00:11:40,899 --> 00:11:41,939
because they don't change.

174
00:11:42,239 --> 00:11:43,559
They aren't affected by anything.

175
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:44,739
But stars

176
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:46,520
are affected by atmospheric interference.

177
00:11:46,619 --> 00:11:47,960
They look like they're twinkling.

178
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:50,380
Look,

179
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,100
it's twinkling, right?

180
00:12:01,439 --> 00:12:03,079
So as long as the distance is far enough,

181
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,300
even the biggest things

182
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:08,460
will seem tiny.

183
00:12:11,380 --> 00:12:12,700
It's the same with human worries.

184
00:12:15,939 --> 00:12:16,939
Shixian.

185
00:12:18,199 --> 00:12:19,199
Your nights

186
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,760
should be reserved for beautiful things,

187
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:24,760
like the ocean,

188
00:12:27,119 --> 00:12:28,119
like the stars,

189
00:12:30,859 --> 00:12:32,039
not spent at Blue Moon,

190
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:39,520
and certainly not on some

191
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:41,399
insignificant people.

192
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:55,680
But,

193
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:00,340
but I still need to make money.

194
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,640
Then make it tomorrow.

195
00:13:07,060 --> 00:13:08,060
Here,

196
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:09,340
let's play with this tonight.

197
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:12,899
Where did you get this?

198
00:13:13,239 --> 00:13:14,239
I stole it.

199
00:13:18,319 --> 00:13:19,479
Then let's light it together.

200
00:13:26,399 --> 00:13:26,899
Pretty?

201
00:13:27,293 --> 00:13:28,293
Yes.

202
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:01,960
Teng Mo.

203
00:14:03,020 --> 00:14:04,020
Thank you.

204
00:14:25,079 --> 00:14:26,840
Search every single booth!

205
00:14:27,199 --> 00:14:28,199
Today,

206
00:14:28,479 --> 00:14:30,439
even if I have to turn
this place upside down,

207
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:32,300
I will find that bastard.

208
00:15:07,539 --> 00:15:08,539
Throw them out!

209
00:15:42,319 --> 00:15:42,779
Are you okay?

210
00:15:43,119 --> 00:15:44,119
I'm fine, I'm fine.

211
00:15:45,659 --> 00:15:47,215
Be careful, there might be
glass shards in your clothes.

212
00:15:47,239 --> 00:15:48,239
Are you guys okay?

213
00:15:48,439 --> 00:15:49,439
We're fine.

214
00:15:50,020 --> 00:15:50,560
Are you alright?

215
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:50,979
Well...

216
00:15:51,359 --> 00:15:52,359
I...

217
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:54,036
I'll just go back and
put some ointment on it.

218
00:15:54,060 --> 00:15:55,060
Clean myself up.

219
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:57,560
Teng Mo,

220
00:16:03,039 --> 00:16:03,920
I'm going to step out for a moment.

221
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:04,460
Go on, hurry.

222
00:16:04,479 --> 00:16:05,479
Go ahead.

223
00:16:08,439 --> 00:16:09,300
We're closed for today.

224
00:16:09,399 --> 00:16:10,559
Please come back another day.

225
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:24,680
Let me do it.

226
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:45,460
Does it hurt?

227
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,500
It's okay.

228
00:16:53,060 --> 00:16:54,220
What on earth happened today?

229
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:58,120
Someone just came to catch a mistress.

230
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:00,680
No wonder.

231
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:02,460
Barging around like crazy.

232
00:17:05,279 --> 00:17:07,279
You shouldn't be so
impulsive in the future.

233
00:17:08,739 --> 00:17:10,880
A glass cut to the neck is no joke.

234
00:17:13,199 --> 00:17:14,599
I wasn't thinking much at the time.

235
00:17:20,359 --> 00:17:21,460
Why were you late today?

236
00:17:25,699 --> 00:17:27,359
Don't I usually come around this time?

237
00:17:29,206 --> 00:17:31,366
Usually, you're here right
when my performance starts.

238
00:17:34,060 --> 00:17:35,940
I got held up by some
things at the shop today.

239
00:17:41,899 --> 00:17:42,899
So...

240
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:45,300
were you...

241
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:47,079
rushing over just to see me?

242
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:51,819
Half and half.

243
00:17:52,819 --> 00:17:54,020
Half of it is because...

244
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:56,819
you got hurt because of me.

245
00:17:58,340 --> 00:17:59,340
And the other half?

246
00:18:02,873 --> 00:18:03,873
I have no more Vandacon.

247
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:05,560
You still...

248
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:10,140
You still want to take it?

249
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:15,580
Is that all you wanted to ask me?

250
00:18:20,260 --> 00:18:21,920
Can you stop working there in the future?

251
00:18:23,899 --> 00:18:24,899
Why?

252
00:18:26,819 --> 00:18:28,739
Although Blue Moon Bar
is a legitimate business,

253
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:30,700
it still attracts all kinds of people.

254
00:18:30,939 --> 00:18:32,578
If that bottle had hit you today,

255
00:18:32,579 --> 00:18:33,579
what would you have done?

256
00:18:34,579 --> 00:18:37,299
Do you love poking your nose into
other people's business that much?

257
00:18:38,340 --> 00:18:39,340
Yes.

258
00:18:39,439 --> 00:18:40,560
I was being nosy.

259
00:18:42,039 --> 00:18:43,039
Wait here.

260
00:18:44,899 --> 00:18:45,899
Here.

261
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,080
Didn't you want to buy Vandacon?

262
00:18:49,380 --> 00:18:50,380
Here you go.

263
00:19:08,260 --> 00:19:09,539
It's not what you think.

264
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:28,600
Brother Mo.

265
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:29,960
Whiskey...?

266
00:19:30,020 --> 00:19:31,020
Just a beer, please.

267
00:19:31,180 --> 00:19:32,180
Sure.

268
00:19:38,220 --> 00:19:39,220
Thanks.

269
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:01,520
Go wait outside.

270
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:06,840
Brother Mo.

271
00:20:07,060 --> 00:20:08,060
I'll head over there.

272
00:20:11,399 --> 00:20:12,399
Brother Hao.

273
00:20:12,819 --> 00:20:14,119
What brings you here?

274
00:20:14,739 --> 00:20:15,739
Nothing much.

275
00:20:16,060 --> 00:20:17,800
Just brought the boys out to have some fun.

276
00:20:18,140 --> 00:20:19,140
Then have a great time!

277
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:20,560
I'm sorry, sir.

278
00:20:20,779 --> 00:20:22,859
Today's VIP booths have
already been reserved.

279
00:20:23,899 --> 00:20:25,736
What guest could be more
important than Brother Hao?

280
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:26,079
Go ahead.

281
00:20:26,479 --> 00:20:26,960
Okay.

282
00:20:27,199 --> 00:20:27,579
Brother Hao,

283
00:20:27,739 --> 00:20:28,739
I'll get it sorted out.

284
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:41,819
Just a guy from the streets.

285
00:20:42,319 --> 00:20:43,319
An old acquaintance.

286
